<h1>
Coexistence and Access Etiquette in the US Unlicensed PCS Band
</h1>
<strong>
David G. Steer
</strong>

<p><b>One-line summary:</b>
A set of etiquette rules to allow multiple systems to coexist in unlicensed PCS band, which is subdivided into "asynchronous" and "isochronous" (slotted) subbands.
</p>

<h2>Overview/Main Points</h2>
<ul>
<li> Listen before transmit (from 750us in async to 10ms in sync)
<li> Limit transmitter power
<li> Limit duration of single transmission, then backoff to allow others
<li> Limit duration of total conversation (8 hrs)
<li> Limit xmit BW: >50KHz async, >500KHz isochronous
<li> Isochr band divided into eight 1.25MHz channels
<li> U-PCS band is tucked between the send and receive bands for licensed PCS
</ul>

<h2>Relevance</h2>
Feh.

<h2>Flaws</h2>
A laundry list of factoids, quantities, specs, etc.  The high order bits above are all we really care about.

